<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7636&amp;p=76407#p76407"><![CDATA[
I'm pretty sure a US FDS would have seen a FDS System Cartridge which would connect to the Drive via the expansion port pins that route to the cartridge connector. It would have been able to mix audio just fine. No cable from the cartridge to the Disk Drive would have been needed. <br /><br />I know piracy is cited as the issue for FDS not even being tried here but I would think that would have been much less of an issue in North America at the time. But if Japanese developers can't market the game also in Japan without piracy plus Nintendo's horrible licensing, it's no wonder it never happened.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sat Apr 09, 2011 1:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
