<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7636&amp;p=76404#p76404"><![CDATA[
Look at the number of "to cart" signals on the expansion port. Then look at the number of signals on the cable from the Family Computer Disk System's RAM adapter to the disk drive. I'm pretty sure the expansion port was originally intended for the FDS until Nintendo scrapped the North American counterpart of the FDS due to widespread illicit copying.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Apr 09, 2011 11:36 am</p><hr />
